caller_intent: The caller is seeking a homeowners insurance quote for a house they are purchasing, having previously discussed auto and renters insurance with the agent.
resolution_steps: Agent confirms the caller's intent to obtain a homeowners insurance quote for a specific property.
Agent requests property details (address, number of bedrooms/baths, construction type).
Agent explains the process of sending the information to the quote team for evaluation after hours.
Agent arranges to send an email with a video explanation of the quotes and requests confirmation of the roof replacement date (2018) and closing date (November 3rd).
Agent offers to coordinate with the caller's current auto insurer for potential bundling.
knowledge_required: Homeowners insurance underwriting criteria (roof age, property features, pets)
Quote generation process and follow-up timelines
summary: Lina McFarlane assists a caller in initiating a homeowners insurance quote for a new property, gathering necessary details and arranging follow-up communication. The caller agrees to confirm roof replacement date and closing date, with a promised callback on Monday. The agent also mentions potential bundling with the caller's existing auto insurance.
